# Framework development (this repo)

## Two clones

| Clone | Role |
|-------|------|
| **Dev** (this repo) | Edit framework, run tests, push to GitHub — **no `memory/`** |
| **Install** (`install_root` in `dev.config.json`) | Cursor skills/hooks + `$MEMORY_HOME` |

`dev.config.json` is gitignored. Never commit `memory/` or user data in dev.

## After code changes

```bash
bash scripts/sync-to-install.sh
bash tests/run-tests.sh
```

Relink if `SKILL.md` or hooks changed: `bash scripts/link-cursor-skills.sh --force` from **install** clone.

## Versioning

Behaviour changes require `bash scripts/bump-version.sh` + `CHANGELOG.md` — see [VERSIONING.md](../VERSIONING.md).

## Paths

- `$FRAMEWORK_ROOT` → install clone (Cursor symlink target)
- `$MEMORY_HOME` → `<install>/memory/`
- External writes **only** under `~/.cursor/` (hooks, skills, env)

Single entry skill: `@agent-memory`. Distill-first sync — scan, ask user, then run.
